40|$|Amorphous tin {{selenide}} {{thin films}} which possess <b>Ovonic</b> type switching properties are fabricated using vacuum deposition techniques. The devices are fabricated in a planar configuration and consist of amorphous tin selenide deposited over silver contacts. Results obtained indicate that <b>Ovonic</b> type memory switching does occur in these films {{with the energy}} density required for switching from a high impedance to a low impedance state being dependent on the spacing between the electrodes of the device. There is also a strong implication that the switching {{is a function of}} the magnitude of the applied voltage pulse...|$|R
